Preámbulo (español)
-------------------

Roomie es software "source-available". Puedes leer el código, auditarlo,
modificarlo y usarlo para fines personales o sin ánimo de lucro sin pagar
nada. Para usarlo con fines comerciales necesitas una licencia comercial
separada y pagada al autor. Las contribuciones al proyecto son bienvenidas
y se rigen por los mismos términos.

Este texto en español es una guía. En caso de conflicto, prevalece el
texto en inglés que aparece a continuación.

Preamble (English)
------------------

Roomie is source-available software. You may read, audit, modify, and
use it for Personal Purposes or Non-Commercial Purposes at no cost.
Commercial Use requires a separate, paid commercial license granted by
the Author. Contributions are welcome and are governed by this same
license.


1. Grant of Rights
------------------

Subject to the terms below, the Author grants You a worldwide,
royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to:

  (a) View and audit the source code of the Software;

  (b) Use the Software for Personal Purposes and Non-Commercial
      Purposes;

  (c) Modify the Software and create derivative works for Personal
      Purposes and Non-Commercial Purposes;

  (d) Distribute unmodified or modified copies of the Software,
      provided that every recipient receives a copy of this license
      unchanged, the copyright notice is preserved, and the recipient's
      intended use is Personal or Non-Commercial;

  (e) Submit contributions (patches, pull requests, issues) to the
      upstream project hosted by the Author.


2. Definitions
--------------

"Software" means the source code, compiled artifacts, assets, and
documentation distributed under this license, including the "Roomie"
project and any file that references this license.

"Author" means Abraham Leiro, the copyright holder.

"You" means any individual or legal entity exercising rights under
this license.

"Personal Purposes" means use by a natural person for private,
non-professional activities, including learning, experimentation,
hobby projects, and private research.

"Non-Commercial Purposes" means any use that does not directly or
indirectly generate revenue, commercial advantage, or monetary
compensation for You or for any third party. Non-Commercial Purposes
include academic use by students and teachers, research at
non-profit institutions, and internal tooling inside registered
non-profit organizations.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software or its output that is
neither Personal nor Non-Commercial. Commercial Use includes, without
limitation:

  - running the Software as part of a paid product or service;
  - offering hosted instances of the Software to third parties
    (Software-as-a-Service);
  - using the Software within the internal operations of a for-profit
    company, including internal tooling, even if not redistributed;
  - using the output produced by the Software (including generated
    marketing campaigns, emails, strategies, audits, and creative
    content) in any revenue-generating activity;
  - incorporating the Software or substantial portions of it into
    another product that is distributed or operated commercially.


3. Commercial Licensing
-----------------------

Commercial Use of the Software requires a separate, paid commercial
license granted in writing by the Author. To obtain one, contact the
Author at the address provided in the project's README.

You may evaluate the Software for Commercial Use for a maximum of
thirty (30) days from the date You first run it. After that period,
continued Commercial Use without a signed commercial license is a
violation of this license.


